1
00:00:15,432 --> 00:00:17,892
<b><font color="#D900D9">[FAINT GROANING]</font></b>

2
00:00:18,727 --> 00:00:20,937
<b><font color="#808080">EVE:</font></b> I never felt like that before.

3
00:00:21,354 --> 00:00:22,354
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GROANS]</font></b>

4
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:23,772
That was...

5
00:00:24,065 --> 00:00:25,275
<b><font color="#808080">LUCIFER:</font></b> Exhilarating.

6
00:00:26,776 --> 00:00:29,106
<b><font color="#808080">EVE:</font></b> That man was so terrible.

7
00:00:29,654 --> 00:00:30,654
<b><font color="#808080">LUCIFER:</font></b> Truly evil.

8
00:00:32,991 --> 00:00:34,491
<b><font color="#808080">EVE:</font></b> We made him pay.

9
00:00:34,576 --> 00:00:35,576
Please.

10
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:38,116
Who can we punish next?

11
00:00:38,204 --> 00:00:39,204
<b><font color="#D900D9">[BANG]</font></b>

12
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:43,585
I want to feel like that again.

13
00:00:44,127 --> 00:00:47,627
Yes, it's quite the rush,
finally being who I'm meant to be.

14
00:00:48,757 --> 00:00:53,177
But, sadly, my dear,
criminals don't line up to be punished.

15
00:00:56,347 --> 00:00:58,677
So that's why you work with the LAPD.

16
00:00:58,975 --> 00:01:00,845
It all makes so much sense now.

17
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:05,395
You use them to find the bad guys.

18
00:01:07,734 --> 00:01:08,944
Well, I want in.

19
00:01:11,279 --> 00:01:12,279
Ah!

20
00:01:12,947 --> 00:01:14,617
- Do you now, darling?
- Mm-hmm.

21
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:17,539
Maybe we could do it together.

22
00:01:18,286 --> 00:01:22,166
Find the worst of the worst
and give them what they deserve.

23
00:01:24,209 --> 00:01:27,089
<b><font color="#D900D9">[EVE SIGHS]</font></b>

24
00:01:29,422 --> 00:01:32,342
<b><font color="#808080">CHLOE:</font></b> So, Julian, you admit to...

25
00:01:32,634 --> 00:01:36,014
human trafficking
and to the murder of Gary Van Blunt

26
00:01:36,387 --> 00:01:38,097
and officer John Reyes.

27
00:01:38,181 --> 00:01:39,181
Yes.

28
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,270
You're going to jail
for a really long time, cop killer.

29
00:01:43,728 --> 00:01:46,018
- At least I'll be safe there.
- What?

30
00:01:47,023 --> 00:01:50,573
If you didn't break your back falling down
a hill, we need to know about that now.

31
00:01:50,652 --> 00:01:51,742
I fell down the hill.

32
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:54,950
I f... fell down the hill, I sw...
I swear!

33
00:01:56,032 --> 00:01:57,032
<b><font color="#D900D9">[WHISPERING]</font></b> Chloe.

34
00:01:57,408 --> 00:01:59,408
<b><font color="#D900D9">[JULIAN SNIFFS]</font></b>

35
00:02:00,161 --> 00:02:01,321
<b><font color="#D900D9">[CHLOE WHISPERING]</font></b> What's up?

36
00:02:01,579 --> 00:02:02,659
Julian's reaction.

37
00:02:03,623 --> 00:02:04,923
Does it look familiar to you?

38
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:07,877
- Huh?
- Like people we've seen before

39
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:10,381
after a certain consultant
has been left alone with them.

40
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:11,673
What do you mean?

41
00:02:12,423 --> 00:02:14,263
- I think Lucifer did this.
- That's crazy.

42
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:16,592
You know what's crazy?
How much Lucifer gets away with.

43
00:02:16,678 --> 00:02:17,758
I'm sick of it. Aren't you?

44
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:20,064
Lucifer wouldn't do this.
He wouldn't go this far.

45
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:22,100
He would never take justice
into his own hands?

46
00:02:22,183 --> 00:02:24,495
Especially as a cop was killed
because of his stupid recklessness.

47
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:25,979
You need to cut him some slack.

48
00:02:26,521 --> 00:02:29,771
You have had a target on his back
ever since...

49
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:32,442
well...

50
00:02:33,778 --> 00:02:34,778
Charlotte.

51
00:02:36,531 --> 00:02:40,331
I'm just not sure if you're looking
at this objectively.

52
00:02:40,410 --> 00:02:41,410
That's all.

53
00:02:42,328 --> 00:02:43,328
Like you are?

54
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:56,470
<b><font color="#808080">REMY:</font></b> I could understand Lucifer
callously ignoring our duty

55
00:02:56,551 --> 00:02:58,641
to keep humans and the divine separate.

56
00:02:59,262 --> 00:03:00,262
But you?

57
00:03:00,346 --> 00:03:01,596
How could you do this?

58
00:03:01,764 --> 00:03:02,764
A child...

59
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:03,731
with a human?

60
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:05,272
Wonderful human.

61
00:03:06,895 --> 00:03:09,225
I know how difficult this
must be for you. All right?

62
00:03:09,564 --> 00:03:11,154
I used to be just like you.

63
00:03:11,524 --> 00:03:15,074
Looking down on humans
as if they were ants.

64
00:03:15,945 --> 00:03:18,235
But we need to realize
that we are not above them.

65
00:03:19,115 --> 00:03:20,195
I am above them.

66
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:21,408
But you...

67
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,827
You don't even have your
powers anymore, do you?

68
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:27,543
No, I can no longer
slow time and I'm glad.

69
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:30,544
My powers, they kept me at a distance,

70
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:33,047
kept me disconnected from humanity.

71
00:03:33,129 --> 00:03:36,419
And I think that's why they're gone now.
Because I don't want that anymore.

72
00:03:36,507 --> 00:03:38,007
You were the one who taught me

73
00:03:38,092 --> 00:03:40,472
that celestials and humans
need to be separate.

74
00:03:40,553 --> 00:03:44,353
Yes, Remy, I did,
and now I am telling you

75
00:03:44,766 --> 00:03:45,886
that I was wrong.

76
00:03:48,770 --> 00:03:49,810
Let me show you.

77
00:03:57,445 --> 00:03:59,695
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SOUND OF CAR DOORS]</font></b>

78
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:02,161
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SOUND OF A CAMERA]</font></b>

79
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:04,487
Hey, Ella, who do we have?

80
00:04:05,411 --> 00:04:06,411
Hey, Chloe.

81
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:10,119
Victim died from a gunshot
straight to the head up on that bridge.

82
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:12,288
But apparently murdering wasn't enough.

83
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:14,837
So they tossed his body over the bridge
like day-old garbage.

84
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:17,921
Broke nearly every bone in his body
from the looks of it.

85
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:19,049
<b><font color="#808080">CHLOE:</font></b> Hmm.

86
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:21,343
Are you okay?

87
00:04:22,136 --> 00:04:23,716
Just death. People die.

88
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:25,180
Mm-hmm.

89
00:04:25,390 --> 00:04:26,560
Well, we just deal with it.

90
00:04:28,434 --> 00:04:30,274
Anyhow,
what do we know about this guy?

91
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:31,443
<b><font color="#808080">ELLA:</font></b> Sam Zofrelli.

92
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:34,111
Rap sheet filled with
drug possession charges.

93
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:36,400
Oh! We also found traces of cocaine

94
00:04:36,484 --> 00:04:38,534
in his pockets,
but no sign of drug use.

95
00:04:38,611 --> 00:04:40,241
So I'm thinking probably dealer.

96
00:04:40,321 --> 00:04:43,741
- So you think this was about drugs?
- Maybe. Pockets were empty.

97
00:04:43,908 --> 00:04:45,948
Keys, wallet, all gone.

98
00:04:46,202 --> 00:04:47,832
But the body was here for hours

99
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:50,002
so could have been taken
by anyone brave enough

100
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:51,671
to frisk a corpse this effed-up.

101
00:04:51,749 --> 00:04:53,499
But why throw a body over a bridge

102
00:04:53,584 --> 00:04:54,674
that's already dead?

103
00:04:54,752 --> 00:04:55,802
Where's Lucifer?

104
00:04:56,087 --> 00:04:59,047
Oh, he's been ignoring me actually.

105
00:05:01,217 --> 00:05:02,637
Oh, he's with Eve.

106
00:05:03,052 --> 00:05:05,762
Yes, probably with Eve.
What you think of her?

107
00:05:05,930 --> 00:05:09,890
I think that she's rubbing off on him
and not necessarily in a good way.

108
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:12,646
Good morning, Detective.

109
00:05:13,938 --> 00:05:16,188
Please don't tell me she's behind me.

110
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:18,028
She's behind you.

111
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:21,855
Hello.

112
00:05:21,946 --> 00:05:22,816
Lucifer.

113
00:05:22,905 --> 00:05:25,195
This is a crime scene.
No visitors. No offense, Eve.

114
00:05:25,366 --> 00:05:26,946
Eve wants the same thing we do.

115
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:28,285
- Catch a killer.
- Yes.

116
00:05:28,369 --> 00:05:30,869
I am here to learn from you, Chloe.

117
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:33,825
I want to know everything there is
to know about catching criminals.

118
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:38,800
Especially the very, very bad ones.

119
00:05:39,589 --> 00:05:40,669
Can I talk to you, alone?

120
00:05:41,215 --> 00:05:42,625
<b><font color="#D900D9">[EVE GIGGLES]</font></b> Of course.

121
00:05:47,221 --> 00:05:48,351
This isn't gonna work.

122
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:51,731
I agree. A gingham pocket square can
be a bit aggressive, but I'm feeling it.

123
00:05:51,893 --> 00:05:54,313
- No. Eve being here, not OK.
- Why not?

124
00:05:55,188 --> 00:05:57,978
You can't just join a
case for the fun of it.

125
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:00,146
We are solving a murder.
This is serious.

126
00:06:00,234 --> 00:06:01,744
Oh, I agree. Very serious.

127
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:04,491
If that's how you feel,
I completely understand.

128
00:06:05,239 --> 00:06:06,239
Where are you going?

129
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:09,366
If you don't want us here,
we'll find the killer on our own.

130
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,116
You can't do that.

131
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,208
Oh, yes we can.

132
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,500
Okay, fine.

133
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:19,711
Fine. Eve can ride along
just for this case.

134
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:21,756
<b><font color="#D900D9">[EVE SQUEALS]</font></b> Exciting!

135
00:06:21,964 --> 00:06:22,974
<b><font color="#D900D9">[LUCIFER LAUGHS]</font></b>

136
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:26,513
This is going to be so much fun.

137
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:38,437
<b><font color="#808080">EVE:</font></b> Lucifer,
this guy looks really guilty.

138
00:06:39,857 --> 00:06:40,937
What about this guy?

139
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:43,694
That's one mean looking face.

140
00:06:45,696 --> 00:06:48,866
- We should punish them.
- One criminal at a time, dear.

141
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:51,367
<b><font color="#D900D9">[PHONE BUZZES]</font></b>

142
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,250
<b><font color="#808080">CHLOE:</font></b> Decker.

143
00:06:55,164 --> 00:06:57,174
No, I will not accept his call.

144
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:00,419
Who was that?

145
00:07:02,046 --> 00:07:03,046
Nobody.

146
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:07,931
Ah-ah-ah!

147
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:11,313
<b><font color="#808080">DAN:</font></b> Lucifer's bringing his girlfriend
on cases now, huh?

148
00:07:11,597 --> 00:07:12,717
She's actually really sweet.

149
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:14,773
Anyway, you know what?

150
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:17,401
Why not do whatever
makes you happy?

151
00:07:17,728 --> 00:07:20,358
Because any second, bam!
You can get hit

152
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,400
by a chunk of blue
ice from an airplane

153
00:07:22,483 --> 00:07:26,073
or get blown up into a million
pieces by some crazed killer.

154
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:28,744
Or you could mysteriously
break your spinal cord

155
00:07:28,823 --> 00:07:31,203
and become, you know, paralyzed.

156
00:07:32,034 --> 00:07:32,874
Yeah.

157
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:36,285
Is anybody investigating what
happened to Julian McCaffrey?

158
00:07:36,581 --> 00:07:38,831
Nobody's buying his
"I fell down the hill" story, right?

159
00:07:38,916 --> 00:07:41,356
He didn't file any charges,
so there's nothing to investigate.

160
00:07:41,419 --> 00:07:42,879
Even if we wanted to,

161
00:07:43,171 --> 00:07:46,721
remember that house he lived in?
It's probably been professionally cleaned.

162
00:07:47,675 --> 00:07:48,675
You're right.

163
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,010
You're absolutely right.

164
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:56,228
Oh, that's Daniel.

165
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:57,349
He's a douche again.

166
00:07:57,768 --> 00:07:59,398
<b><font color="#808080">EVE:</font></b> Oh, shall we punish him too?

167
00:07:59,687 --> 00:08:01,807
Believe me, his existence
is punishment enough.

168
00:08:02,231 --> 00:08:03,231
<b><font color="#D900D9">[EVE GIGGLES]</font></b>

169
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:06,985
Hey, Ella. What do we have?

170
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:11,737
Well, we still don't know why Sam's
body was tossed off the bridge.

171
00:08:11,949 --> 00:08:14,869
Because the killer is a maniacal
monster who needs to be taken down.

172
00:08:15,661 --> 00:08:16,951
<b><font color="#808080">ELLA:</font></b> Er... maybe.

173
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:21,707
But I did discover that the killer
pistol-whipped poor Sam before he died.

174
00:08:21,792 --> 00:08:23,922
- Sounds like it could be personal.
- And aggressive.

175
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:25,423
And cruel.

176
00:08:25,755 --> 00:08:29,585
And a mistake,
because I was able to recover something

177
00:08:29,675 --> 00:08:31,385
from the gun marks on his face.

178
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:33,601
Gold flakes.

179
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,059
- Gold flakes?
- Mm-hmm.

180
00:08:35,264 --> 00:08:38,234
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GASPS]</font></b> In there? That's amazing.

181
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:41,059
Ah! Well, you know,
I'm just doing my job.

182
00:08:41,604 --> 00:08:43,734
Do you get to be there
for the punishment too?

183
00:08:44,273 --> 00:08:46,113
Er, no.

184
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:47,694
Golden gun.

185
00:08:48,569 --> 00:08:51,359
It's unique and it sounds familiar.

186
00:08:51,447 --> 00:08:53,157
Yes, Roger Moore's Bond films.

187
00:08:53,241 --> 00:08:55,951
Perhaps our killer's Scaramanga,
the man with three nipples.

188
00:08:56,744 --> 00:08:57,584
Maybe.

189
00:08:57,662 --> 00:08:59,792
Ella, do you remember
there was a hitman...

190
00:09:00,164 --> 00:09:02,754
or something who carries a golden pistol.
Do you remember that?

191
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:04,213
<b><font color="#808080">ELLA:</font></b> Ah, let me see.

192
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:06,384
Er... ooh, right here.

193
00:09:06,587 --> 00:09:09,297
Greg Grabowski...

194
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:11,932
and goes by the nickname "Pony Boy".

195
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:14,510
Pony Boy? Stay gold indeed.

196
00:09:14,595 --> 00:09:17,055
And you're never able to pin him down
because he's so good.

197
00:09:17,139 --> 00:09:18,929
But if this wasn't a hit
and it was personal,

198
00:09:19,016 --> 00:09:20,976
it would explain why he was so sloppy.

199
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:22,060
He sounds terrible.

200
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:25,273
- Let's go punish him!
- You mean, bring him to justice.

201
00:09:26,148 --> 00:09:27,228
That's what I said.

202
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:30,114
<b><font color="#808080">LUCIFER:</font></b> Oh!
That clears that up. Come on.

203
00:09:33,489 --> 00:09:35,779
When I was a newborn demon...

204
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:39,119
I was smaller than my opponents.

205
00:09:40,037 --> 00:09:41,537
But I was fast.

206
00:09:42,498 --> 00:09:45,288
So I used my speed, kept low...

207
00:09:46,752 --> 00:09:49,132
and always went for
the major arteries.

208
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:52,343
With my first vanquished
foe on his knees,

209
00:09:52,508 --> 00:09:54,548
I slit my blade across his throat.

210
00:09:54,844 --> 00:09:58,604
I felt the heat from his blood
dripping down my face.

211
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:05,397
And then a stranger heat in my loins.

212
00:10:05,479 --> 00:10:07,229
Okay.

213
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:12,244
When I mentioned that the baby could
hear everything from inside the womb

214
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:14,613
I imagined introducing
him to things like

215
00:10:14,697 --> 00:10:15,867
classical music...

216
00:10:16,490 --> 00:10:18,080
and stories...

217
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:23,290
that aren't about graphic murders.

218
00:10:23,372 --> 00:10:26,672
Why would you want to hear a story
not about graphic murder?

219
00:10:28,544 --> 00:10:30,004
We can talk about that later.

220
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,170
- I have to go to work.
- Great.

221
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:33,840
Give me a second to get my knives.

222
00:10:37,511 --> 00:10:38,971
Maze, sweetie.

223
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:41,934
You can't come to work with me.

224
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:43,390
<b><font color="#808080">MAZE:</font></b> I have to!

225
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:48,226
Do you know all the things that could
happen to you or your baby out there?

226
00:10:48,314 --> 00:10:49,984
Er... heartburn?

227
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:51,066
<b><font color="#D900D9">[RING OF METAL]</font></b>

228
00:10:51,108 --> 00:10:53,688
You could get gunned down
in a drive-by shooting, Linda.

229
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:57,530
Or kidnapped by a cartel who use
women as drug mules,

230
00:10:57,698 --> 00:11:00,278
not to mention what an angel baby
will fetch on the black market.

231
00:11:01,035 --> 00:11:02,035
How comforting.

232
00:11:02,119 --> 00:11:04,409
You said I'm part of this family, Linda.

233
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:05,997
So I'm going to protect you.

234
00:11:06,082 --> 00:11:08,422
Maze, the people
I am seeing this afternoon

235
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:11,301
are a vegan chef
who compulsively shoplifts...

236
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:13,921
and a record producer
who wets the bed.

237
00:11:14,423 --> 00:11:15,423
- But I...
- Maze...

238
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:17,223
I don't need protecting.

239
00:11:20,304 --> 00:11:24,104
<b><font color="#D900D9">["WE LOVE IT" BY OUTASIGHT PLAYING]</font></b>

240
