his finger to pry a ring off.

440
00:21:22,614 --> 00:21:24,874
Probably whoever
stole all his money and drugs.

441
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:27,195
Mm. Mm-hmm. Yeah.

442
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:28,866
Er, you okay?

443
00:21:30,664 --> 00:21:33,544
Do you think there is such a
thing as celestial justice?

444
00:21:34,543 --> 00:21:37,883
Because if celestial
justice does exist,

445
00:21:37,963 --> 00:21:39,593
like heaven and hell,

446
00:21:39,673 --> 00:21:43,303
then what we've been doing here,
say arresting criminals...

447
00:21:44,177 --> 00:21:45,217
why even bother?

448
00:21:47,055 --> 00:21:50,845
I know you're religious and I thought
you may have some thoughts on it.

449
00:21:51,727 --> 00:21:55,477
Well, I was religious

450
00:21:55,856 --> 00:21:57,106
- and...
- Oh.

451
00:21:57,232 --> 00:22:00,992
...when I used to believe
in all that stuff,

452
00:22:01,069 --> 00:22:04,449
I really thought that
I was doing my part

453
00:22:04,531 --> 00:22:06,621
to uphold right and wrong on Earth

454
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:09,410
and everyone would get
their comeuppance eventually,

455
00:22:09,578 --> 00:22:11,408
but we still needed to keep people safe.

456
00:22:12,289 --> 00:22:15,829
But now I believe we are all anybody's got

457
00:22:15,917 --> 00:22:18,417
and if we don't hold people
accountable, nobody will

458
00:22:18,503 --> 00:22:21,213
because heaven and
hell, they don't exist.

459
00:22:21,381 --> 00:22:23,131
But what if they do exist?

460
00:22:23,216 --> 00:22:25,046
- Say, the devil.
- He's not real.

461
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:26,677
Chloe, look at the Bible.

462
00:22:26,762 --> 00:22:28,472
It is so full of contradictions.

463
00:22:28,555 --> 00:22:30,175
Fine.
Take the devil, for example.

464
00:22:30,682 --> 00:22:33,022
The devil's supposed to be pure evil,
right?

465
00:22:33,685 --> 00:22:35,515
But he started out as an angel.

466
00:22:35,812 --> 00:22:39,942
You can't start good
and the turn all evil.

467
00:22:40,025 --> 00:22:41,855
I mean,
that's what they want us to believe?

468
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:42,943
You're right.

469
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:45,196
He's an angel.

470
00:22:46,114 --> 00:22:48,454
No, my point is that it's all bullshit.

471
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:51,872
I...

472
00:22:57,626 --> 00:23:00,416
<b><font color="#808080">AMENADIEL:</font></b> This is where I came
with the mother of my child

473
00:23:00,504 --> 00:23:02,924
right after we found out that
we were going to be parents.

474
00:23:03,006 --> 00:23:04,466
We both realized...

475
00:23:05,509 --> 00:23:07,429
just how wonderful it would be.

476
00:23:07,677 --> 00:23:09,137
<b><font color="#808080">REMY:</font></b> All I see is weakness.

477
00:23:09,471 --> 00:23:10,351
They're pathetic.

478
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:13,980
If you raise your son surrounded by them,
he will become like they are.

479
00:23:14,059 --> 00:23:16,979
They may be flawed,
yes, but so are we

480
00:23:17,562 --> 00:23:19,982
and flawed doesn't mean weak.

481
00:23:20,065 --> 00:23:21,895
Sounds like something
a weak person would say.

482
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:25,947
Amenadiel, I just want
the best for your child.

483
00:23:26,029 --> 00:23:27,029
So do I.

484
00:23:31,910 --> 00:23:32,990
I'm taking the baby.

485
00:23:33,078 --> 00:23:34,908
No, Remy, you're not.

486
00:23:35,831 --> 00:23:37,921
I'll never let you
find him or his mother.

487
00:23:37,999 --> 00:23:38,999
Too late.

488
00:23:39,292 --> 00:23:40,712
I picked up the scent this morning.

489
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:43,376
I've listened to you out of respect,
Amenadiel,

490
00:23:43,463 --> 00:23:44,673
for what you once were.

491
00:23:45,132 --> 00:23:47,262
But I'm convinced more than
ever of what I need to do.

492
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:48,426
Remy.

493
00:23:49,636 --> 00:23:51,886
I won't let you take my child.

494
00:23:52,180 --> 00:23:53,350
Try and stop me.

495
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:55,930
<b><font color="#D900D9">[FLAP OF WINGS]</font></b>

496
00:23:56,143 --> 00:23:57,893
<b><font color="#D900D9">[FLAP OF WINGS]</font></b>

497
00:24:05,819 --> 00:24:08,029
<b><font color="#D900D9">[FAINT TINKLING SOUND]</font></b>

498
00:24:17,122 --> 00:24:19,212
<b><font color="#D900D9">[LOW ROLL OF THUNDER]</font></b>

499
00:24:30,135 --> 00:24:32,345
<b><font color="#D900D9">[LOW ROLL OF THUNDER]</font></b>

500
00:24:38,852 --> 00:24:40,442
<b><font color="#D900D9">[LINDA GASPS]</font></b>

501
00:24:40,604 --> 00:24:42,404
Oh, my. Maze!

502
00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:43,606
What is it?

503
00:24:44,733 --> 00:24:46,493
I thought someone was following me.

504
00:24:46,568 --> 00:24:49,738
- Who?
- You. You are following me.

505
00:24:49,821 --> 00:24:50,861
Why are you following me?

506
00:24:50,947 --> 00:24:52,697
I'm protecting you
when you leave the house.

507
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:54,532
Don't you have
anything else to do?

508
00:24:54,868 --> 00:24:56,498
Like hunting bounty.

509
00:24:56,578 --> 00:24:57,908
I cleared my entire schedule.

510
00:24:57,996 --> 00:24:59,576
I am never leaving your side.

511
00:24:59,664 --> 00:25:01,754
I don't need you to
always be around.

512
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:04,132
I need you to back off.

513
00:25:04,294 --> 00:25:05,294
But...

514
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:08,718
how else am I supposed
to protect our baby?

515
00:25:09,841 --> 00:25:10,841
Our?

516
00:25:12,886 --> 00:25:13,926
Maze, this isn't...

517
00:25:15,305 --> 00:25:17,265
I just need some space. Okay?

518
00:25:18,558 --> 00:25:21,558
Sure. Since we're here,
do you want to grab a coconut water?

519
00:25:28,693 --> 00:25:30,283
<b><font color="#D900D9">[CRASH]</font></b>

520
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:35,242
<b><font color="#D900D9">[ROAR OF RUBBLE FALLING]</font></b>

521
00:25:35,659 --> 00:25:38,749
I will never let you anywhere near Linda
or my son!

522
00:25:38,828 --> 00:25:41,038
Who's gonna stop me? You?

523
00:25:41,456 --> 00:25:43,206
There's only one way to find out.

524
00:25:43,875 --> 00:25:45,415
<b><font color="#D900D9">[WHIPPING OF AIR]</font></b>

525
00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:48,379
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SMASH]</font></b>

526
00:25:51,466 --> 00:25:53,386
Can't have anyone saying
it wasn't a fair fight.

527
00:25:54,261 --> 00:25:57,601
<b><font color="#D900D9">[WHIPPING OF AIR, CLASH OF METAL]</font></b>

528
00:25:58,974 --> 00:26:00,774
I'm not going to let you raise this baby
here,

529
00:26:00,934 --> 00:26:03,134
where everything special about
him will be leached away.

530
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:11,243
He will be special
because he's raised here!

531
00:26:11,361 --> 00:26:13,741
- <b><font color="#D900D9">[AMENADIEL ROARS]</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">[BOOM]</font></b>

532
00:26:14,114 --> 00:26:15,034
With his family.

533
00:26:15,115 --> 00:26:17,525
Funny, I thought I was your family.

534
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:22,325
You are my family, Remy.

535
00:26:22,414 --> 00:26:23,464
But this is my son!

536
00:26:23,540 --> 00:26:24,960
<b><font color="#D900D9">[AMENADIEL GROANS]</font></b>

537
00:26:25,625 --> 00:26:27,625
- <b><font color="#D900D9">[CRASH]</font></b>
- <b><font color="#D900D9">[METAL CLINKS]</font></b>

538
00:26:30,130 --> 00:26:32,050
<b><font color="#D900D9">[BOTH GROANING]</font></b>

539
00:26:36,886 --> 00:26:38,426
<b><font color="#D900D9">[REMY YELLS]</font></b>

540
00:26:39,389 --> 00:26:40,559
<b><font color="#D900D9">[REMY GROANS]</font></b>

541
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:41,640
<b><font color="#D900D9">[REMY GASPS]</font></b>

542
00:26:43,059 --> 00:26:45,189
Earth hasn't made me weak, Remy.

543
00:26:48,648 --> 00:26:49,858
It's made me stronger.

544
00:26:52,652 --> 00:26:53,652
<b><font color="#D900D9">[CLINK]</font></b>

545
00:26:57,949 --> 00:26:59,949
A true warrior admits their defeat.

546
00:27:01,411 --> 00:27:03,001
So you'll respect my wishes?

547
00:27:04,247 --> 00:27:06,367
I will... reluctantly.

548
00:27:07,751 --> 00:27:08,961
But be careful, brother.

549
00:27:09,252 --> 00:27:10,712
I still fear one day...

550
00:27:11,421 --> 00:27:13,211
you'll come to regret your decision.

551
00:27:16,259 --> 00:27:19,599
<b><font color="#D900D9">[WINGS FLUTTER]</font></b>

552
00:27:20,972 --> 00:27:22,522
Hey, Linda.

553
00:27:22,932 --> 00:27:26,522
So I'm just calling because
I'm a little worried...

554
00:27:27,395 --> 00:27:29,685
about Lucifer,
and thought that you might know

555
00:27:29,773 --> 00:27:33,233
what's going on with him. When you get
a chance, call me back. Thanks.

556
00:27:34,736 --> 00:27:36,106
What's wrong with Lucifer?

557
00:27:40,492 --> 00:27:42,162
Is he okay?

558
00:27:42,327 --> 00:27:43,697
Yeah, Lucifer's okay.

559
00:27:44,496 --> 00:27:46,076
I think he's just...

560
00:27:46,456 --> 00:27:48,536
He's just going through
something right now.

561
00:27:48,625 --> 00:27:51,285
Don't you always say that
when somebody's going through something,

562
00:27:51,628 --> 00:27:53,548
that's when they need their friends
the most?

563
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:57,634
You know what?
You're right, monkey.

564
00:27:58,843 --> 00:27:59,843
But...

565
00:28:01,596 --> 00:28:04,926
I'm just not sure that I'm the friend
that Lucifer needs right now.

566
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:11,555
You do your homework.

567
00:28:16,069 --> 00:28:18,779
<b><font color="#808080">LUCIFER:</font></b> Could tie Tiernan
to the anchor of one of his ships.

568
00:28:18,863 --> 00:28:21,703
- <b><font color="#808080">EVE:</font></b> Mm-hmm.
- Or a million paper cuts

569
00:28:21,783 --> 00:28:23,493
from his own hundred-dollar bills.

570
00:28:23,785 --> 00:28:24,655
Great.

571
00:28:24,744 --> 00:28:26,004
Oh, no, actually...

572
00:28:26,454 --> 00:28:30,004
I know a man who owns an emu farm.
They're surprisingly bloodthirsty animals.

573
00:28:30,083 --> 00:28:33,003
Just pick a punishment and let's go.
What's the hold-up?

574
00:28:33,086 --> 00:28:35,296
<b><font color="#808080">LUCIFER:</font></b> All in good time, my darling.

575
00:28:36,256 --> 00:28:39,586
You know how satisfying delayed
gratification is in bed, right?

576
00:28:41,761 --> 00:28:42,891
I think you're stalling.

577
00:28:43,096 --> 00:28:44,096
<b><font color="#D900D9">[LAUGHS]</font></b>

578
00:28:44,514 --> 00:28:45,514
What?

579
00:28:45,765 --> 00:28:46,845
Because of Chloe.

580
00:28:48,518 --> 00:28:49,518
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SIGHING]</font></b> Look...

581
00:28:51,438 --> 00:28:52,438
I like Chloe.

582
00:28:53,189 --> 00:28:54,649
I do, she's great.

583
00:28:54,941 --> 00:28:56,571
But to be honest...

584
00:28:58,611 --> 00:29:00,611
I think she's a bad influence on you.

585
00:29:00,864 --> 00:29:02,454
Oh. <b><font color="#D900D9">[SCOFFS]</font></b>

586
00:29:03,324 --> 00:29:05,374
This has nothing to do
with the detective.

587
00:29:05,452 --> 00:29:07,502
It's just better
when you punish them properly.

588
00:29:07,579 --> 00:29:08,579
Lucifer...

589
00:29:10,915 --> 00:29:14,125
I just want you to be
the best version of yourself.

590
00:29:14,294 --> 00:29:15,304
You know?

591
00:29:15,378 --> 00:29:18,298
That devil I met in the garden.

592
00:29:19,048 --> 00:29:19,918
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SIGHS]</font></b>

593
00:29:20,008 --> 00:29:24,468
I held myself back for so long
and I can see you doing the same...

594
00:29:25,013 --> 00:29:26,063
because of her.

595
00:29:27,265 --> 00:29:31,185
I just think she might be a little
too involved in your life.

596
00:29:31,895 --> 00:29:33,975
- That is preposterous.
- <b><font color="#D900D9">[BELL RINGS]</font></b>

597
00:29:35,565 --> 00:29:36,565
Hi, Lucifer.

598
00:29:36,858 --> 00:29:37,688
Who's this?

599
00:29:37,859 --> 00:29:40,449
That is the detective's offspring.

600
00:29:41,112 --> 00:29:42,702
You have a piano up here?

601
00:29:43,364 --> 00:29:45,204
- Yes, but no! Please!
- <b><font color="#D900D9">[PIANO KEYS CRASH]</font></b>

602
00:29:45,283 --> 00:29:47,483
Please don't touch that.
I don't know where you've been.

603
00:29:47,827 --> 00:29:49,247
<b><font color="#808080">TRIXIE:</font></b> Look at all those books!

604
00:29:49,329 --> 00:29:50,959
Yes, emphasis on the look...

605
00:29:52,081 --> 00:29:53,171
Whoa, a pony.

606
00:29:53,249 --> 00:29:55,499
Be careful with that,
that was a gift from Napoleon.

607
00:29:56,336 --> 00:29:58,546
- Do you have a pet?
- Yeah... No, not really.

608
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:01,550
You have stairs to get to your bedroom.
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GASPS]</font></b>

609
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:04,680
Like a princess.

610
00:30:04,761 --> 00:30:06,221
Like a what?

611
00:30:06,304 --> 00:30:07,644
<b><font color="#D900D9">[EVE GIGGLES]</font></b>

612
00:30:07,722 --> 00:30:08,892
How dare you?

613
00:30:09,307 --> 00:30:11,387
You have a hot tub on your balcony?

614
00:30:12,227 --> 00:30:14,307
No! Please don't jump on that,
it's Italian.

615
00:30:14,395 --> 00:30:16,225
This is the coolest place ever!

616
00:30:16,606 --> 00:30:18,226
Does your mother know you're...

617
00:30:18,316 --> 00:30:19,676
Does your mother know you're here?

618
00:30:21,444 --> 00:30:22,444
Yes?

619
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:24,487
Well, what are you doing here?

620
00:30:25,281 --> 00:30:27,281
I came here to make sure you're okay.

621
00:30:29,619 --> 00:30:31,369
My mom said you needed a friend.

622
00:30:34,791 --> 00:30:38,131
But it looks like you already have one.

623
00:30:39,420 --> 00:30:40,420
Hi.

624
00:30:41,047 --> 00:30:42,047
I'm Eve.

625
00:30:46,928 --> 00:30:47,928
<b><font color="#D900D9">[DOOR CLICKS]</font></b>

626
00:30:49,222 --> 00:30:51,142
Hey. Trixie ready?

627
00:30:52,100 --> 00:30:53,480
Trix, Dad's here.

628
00:30:55,019 --> 00:30:56,099
How's the case going?

629
00:30:56,813 --> 00:30:57,903
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SIGHS]</font></b>

630
00:30:58,273 --> 00:31:00,073
We know who the killer is but...

631
00:31:01,067 --> 00:31:02,067
we don't have proof.

632
00:31:02,235 --> 00:31:03,235
Who is it?

633
00:31:03,319 --> 00:31:05,819
<b><font color="#808080">CHLOE:</font></b> Er, Julian's dad, Jacob Tiernan.

634
00:31:07,407 --> 00:31:08,407
Jacob Tiernan.

635
00:31:08,950 --> 00:31:10,450
What, he killed somebody?

636
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:13,365
He thought that Sam was the one
who broke Julian's back, so...

637
00:31:13,454 --> 00:31:15,584
- Simple revenge motive.
- You're sure about that?

638
00:31:16,165 --> 00:31:17,955
I mean, I didn't think
he was capable of...

639
00:31:19,085 --> 00:31:20,165
- of that.
- Trix.

640
00:31:20,587 --> 00:31:21,587
<b><font color="#808080">CHLOE:</font></b> Trix?

641
00:31:21,671 --> 00:31:22,591
Come on.

642
00:31:22,672 --> 00:31:23,762
<b><font color="#D900D9">[DOOR SLIDES]</font></b>

643
00:31:25,008 --> 00:31:26,008
<b><font color="#808080">CHLOE:</font></b> Dan.

644
00:31:27,719 --> 00:31:28,719
Dan!

645
00:31:29,012 --> 00:31:30,012
Yeah?

646
00:31:33,391 --> 00:31:35,601
- Trixie snuck out and went to Lucifer's.
- What?

647
00:31:36,811 --> 00:31:37,851
Well...

648
00:31:37,937 --> 00:31:39,057
We've got to go find her.

649
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:40,731
Now.

650
00:31:44,444 --> 00:31:45,574
Where do you live?

651
00:31:46,654 --> 00:31:47,654
Here.

652
00:31:48,448 --> 00:31:51,618
- Where are you from?
- Far away. I came here for Lucifer.

653
00:31:51,701 --> 00:31:53,791
Keep the commentary to yourself, lady.

654
00:31:53,870 --> 00:31:56,070
- Have you ever been married?
- Yes, it didn't work out.

655
00:31:56,122 --> 00:31:57,725
- How come?
- We weren't right for each other.

656
00:31:57,749 --> 00:31:59,539
- What do you do for work?
- I don't.

657
00:31:59,834 --> 00:32:01,094
Pretty much just get to be me.

658
00:32:01,836 --> 00:32:03,546
Well, that's kind of cool.

659
00:32:04,547 --> 00:32:06,047
- Favorite color?
- Red. What's yours?

660
00:32:06,132 --> 00:32:07,592
I'm asking the questions.

661
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:11,846
Would you excuse me whilst I do something
less mind-numbingly boring

662
00:32:11,930 --> 00:32:14,180
like color-sort my suits?

663
00:32:17,393 --> 00:32:19,943
Are you the kind of friend
Lucifer needs right now?

664
00:32:23,316 --> 00:32:24,396
I hope so.

665
00:32:26,444 --> 00:32:28,154
I care about him very much.

666
00:32:32,742 --> 00:32:35,122
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SCREAMS]</font></b> Oh, my... Lucifer!

667
00:32:35,703 --> 00:32:38,003
I didn't think there'd be
anyone else here, but...

668
00:32:39,123 --> 00:32:40,543
can't have any witnesses.

669
00:32:40,875 --> 00:32:41,875
Oh, please...

670
00:32:42,627 --> 00:32:44,497
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GLASS SHATTERS]</font></b>

671
00:32:44,587 --> 00:32:46,297
<b><font color="#D900D9">[EVE SCREAMING]</font></b> Let's go! Let's go!

672
00:32:46,381 --> 00:32:49,431
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SPLINTERING OF GLASS]</font></b>

673
00:32:49,509 --> 00:32:50,509
<b><font color="#D900D9">[THUD]</font></b>

674
00:32:51,052 --> 00:32:53,512
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GUN SHOTS]</font></b>

675
00:32:53,846 --> 00:32:54,886
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GROANS]</font></b>

676
00:32:56,140 --> 00:32:57,680
What are you?

677
00:32:59,227 --> 00:33:01,397
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GROANS]</font></b>

678
00:33:01,938 --> 00:33:03,018
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GROANS]</font></b>

679
00:33:03,189 --> 00:33:04,899
Tiernan sent you, didn't he?

680
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:06,113
Yeah.

681
00:33:06,192 --> 00:33:08,112
- <b><font color="#D900D9">[ELEVATOR BELL RINGS]</font></b>
- <b><font color="#808080">DAN:</font></b> Where is she?

682
00:33:08,194 --> 00:33:09,324
Where's Trixie?

683
00:33:09,404 --> 00:33:11,614
She's safe. She's through there.

684
00:33:14,951 --> 00:33:16,081
Mommy! Daddy!

685
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:18,580
<b><font color="#D900D9">[TRIXIE GASPS]</font></b> Sorry.

686
00:33:20,206 --> 00:33:21,496
Monkey, you're okay.

687
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:24,960
You're okay.

688
00:33:27,171 --> 00:33:28,511
<b><font color="#808080">CHLOE:</font></b> I love you, honey.

689
00:33:30,425 --> 00:33:32,425
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SIREN WAILING]</font></b>

690
00:33:47,108 --> 00:33:49,438
I hope you know I would...

691
00:33:50,903 --> 00:33:53,703
I would do anything to protect
that little urchin.

692
00:33:56,951 --> 00:33:57,951
I know.

693
00:33:58,661 --> 00:34:01,371
I also know what you're thinking
of doing to Tiernan.

694
00:34:02,331 --> 00:34:03,581
Especially now.

695
00:34:04,292 --> 00:34:06,752
And you, detective.

696
00:34:07,378 --> 00:34:10,298
Don't you want to punish him?
He almost killed your child.

697
00:34:11,090 --> 00:34:12,090
Yes.

698
00:34:13,384 --> 00:34:14,684
I do, yeah.

699
00:34:14,927 --> 00:34:17,427
But I'm gonna do it by following the rules

700
00:34:17,513 --> 00:34:18,513
because...

701
00:34:19,515 --> 00:34:21,845
I believe in right and wrong and...

702
00:34:22,643 --> 00:34:24,773
and deep down I think that...

703
00:34:26,355 --> 00:34:27,475
you do too.

704
00:34:31,319 --> 00:34:32,319
You're the devil.

705
00:34:33,905 --> 00:34:36,365
But you're also an angel. <b><font color="#D900D9">[SIGHS]</font></b>

706
00:34:37,825 --> 00:34:40,535
I'm not sure that I am an angel anymore.

707
00:34:41,162 --> 00:34:42,292
What do you mean?

708
00:34:43,915 --> 00:34:46,825
After I killed Pierce
when my devil face returned...

709
00:34:47,502 --> 00:34:50,092
I never checked to see
if my wings were still there.

710
00:34:51,631 --> 00:34:52,721
I still haven't.

711
00:34:54,467 --> 00:34:55,717
Afraid that they're gone.

712
00:34:56,219 --> 00:34:57,429
For good reason.

713
00:35:00,264 --> 00:35:01,354
Well, you know...

714
00:35:02,725 --> 00:35:04,015
I think you should look.

715
00:35:06,312 --> 00:35:08,772
Maybe you'll be surprised
at what you find.

716
00:35:11,734 --> 00:35:13,114
<b><font color="#808080">EVE:</font></b> The police are done.

717
00:35:23,246 --> 00:35:24,366
<b><font color="#808080">CHLOE:</font></b> Thank you.

718
00:35:25,915 --> 00:35:27,285
Thank you for Trixie.

719
00:35:29,043 --> 00:35:30,133
You're welcome.

720
00:35:42,765 --> 00:35:44,595
We're going to get this guy, right?

721
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:46,770
I mean...

722
00:35:47,645 --> 00:35:49,475
we've been looking
for the worst of the worst.

723
00:35:49,647 --> 00:35:50,647
Here it is.

724
00:35:55,194 --> 00:35:56,194
You're right.

725
00:35:57,738 --> 00:36:00,408
It's time for Tiernan
to get what he deserves, but...

726
00:36:02,243 --> 00:36:03,793
I need to do this on my own.

727
00:36:05,246 --> 00:36:06,246
It's important to me.

728
00:36:08,332 --> 00:36:09,332
Okay.

729
00:36:14,672 --> 00:36:15,672
You know, I...

730
00:36:17,049 --> 00:36:18,429
I only want us...

731
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:21,011
you...

732
00:36:22,138 --> 00:36:23,138
to be happy.

733
00:36:35,985 --> 00:36:39,065
We have you dead to rights
on attempted murder.

734
00:36:39,197 --> 00:36:41,837
So if you don't help us take down
who really killed Sam Zofrelli...

735
00:36:41,908 --> 00:36:44,448
Well. It was your golden gun
used on the murder

736
00:36:44,577 --> 00:36:46,867
so you might be looking pretty damn good
for that, too.

737
00:36:48,456 --> 00:36:49,456
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SIGHS]</font></b>

738
00:36:50,166 --> 00:36:51,706
Look, I love Julian.

739
00:36:52,251 --> 00:36:54,301
That's why I wanted to be the one
to kill Sam.

740
00:36:54,378 --> 00:36:56,128
But Julian's an idiot.

741
00:36:56,589 --> 00:36:58,509
He gets into trouble all the time...

742
00:36:59,258 --> 00:37:00,588
owed Sam a bunch of money.

743
00:37:00,676 --> 00:37:03,756
Is that why Tiernan thought Sam
was the one to break Julian's spine?

744
00:37:03,846 --> 00:37:04,676
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SIGHS]</font></b>

745
00:37:04,764 --> 00:37:07,184
Tiernan wouldn't give Julian any money
to pay back Sam.

746
00:37:07,266 --> 00:37:09,726
So Julian had to give Sam
whatever he could,

747
00:37:10,061 --> 00:37:11,941
his car, his watch,

748
00:37:12,104 --> 00:37:13,194
family heirlooms.

749
00:37:13,272 --> 00:37:14,362
Family heirlooms?

750
00:37:15,066 --> 00:37:16,066
Yeah.

751
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:18,570
It pissed Tiernan off,
but he still loved the kid.

752
00:37:19,237 --> 00:37:20,487
He's his son after all.

753
00:37:20,696 --> 00:37:22,196
But even after all that,

754
00:37:22,490 --> 00:37:24,771
Julian still couldn't come up
with enough to pay back Sam.

755
00:37:24,825 --> 00:37:27,495
<b><font color="#808080">DAN:</font></b> Right,
so after Julian's spine was broken...

756
00:37:28,496 --> 00:37:30,956
Tiernan thought Sam must have
been the one who did it...

757
00:37:31,582 --> 00:37:33,922
asked for the gun and then
got revenge himself?

758
00:37:34,168 --> 00:37:36,088
Too bad somebody
else crippled Julian.

759
00:37:38,214 --> 00:37:39,214
What do you mean?

760
00:37:39,423 --> 00:37:41,093
Tiernan found out Lucifer did it.

761
00:37:42,426 --> 00:37:44,216
That's why he sent me to kill him.

762
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:47,699
We thought that Tiernan was upset because
of Lucifer's behavior in the office.

763
00:37:47,723 --> 00:37:50,893
Where did he get the idea that Lucifer
was the one to break his back?

764
00:37:58,442 --> 00:37:59,442
No idea.

765
00:38:00,152 --> 00:38:02,952
<b><font color="#D900D9">[CHLOE SIGHS]</font></b> All right.
You said family heirlooms, right?

766
00:38:03,239 --> 00:38:05,319
Would that also include a family ring?

767
00:38:07,785 --> 00:38:08,785
All right.

768
00:38:09,704 --> 00:38:10,704
<b><font color="#D900D9">[CLICK]</font></b>

769
00:38:11,289 --> 00:38:12,749
Have you heard from Pony Boy?

770
00:38:12,915 --> 00:38:13,915
Not yet.

771
00:38:15,793 --> 00:38:17,253
It's time to get to the jet.

772
00:38:18,045 --> 00:38:19,415
Leave town for a while.

773
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:26,050
<b><font color="#D900D9">[CRASH]</font></b>

774
00:38:27,805 --> 00:38:29,385
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SHOUTS]</font></b> What the hell was that?

775
00:38:31,892 --> 00:38:33,442
Hello again, Tiernan.

776
00:38:33,853 --> 00:38:35,563
I told you this wasn't over.

777
00:38:36,647 --> 00:38:38,267
<b><font color="#D900D9">[CRASH]</font></b>

778
00:38:39,025 --> 00:38:40,025
Finally.

779
00:38:41,444 --> 00:38:44,824
It's time for you to receive
the punishment that you deserve.

780
00:38:46,532 --> 00:38:47,532
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GASPS]</font></b>

781
00:38:52,330 --> 00:38:54,670
What about that ring?

782
00:38:55,291 --> 00:38:58,171
No, the ring that Tiernan had on
had a family crest on it.

783
00:38:58,252 --> 00:39:01,712
Do you guys really think he would
wear it after taking it off a dead body?

784
00:39:01,797 --> 00:39:02,917
It was a family ring,

785
00:39:03,007 --> 00:39:05,927
so I t think Tiernan saw it as something
that was taken from him.

786
00:39:06,010 --> 00:39:09,810
So if we can prove that Sam had the ring
on his finger before he was killed

787
00:39:09,889 --> 00:39:12,429
and that it's now on Tiernan's hand,
we can arrest him.

788
00:39:13,601 --> 00:39:15,191
Before anyone else gets to him.

789
00:39:15,269 --> 00:39:16,519
I think I've found it.

790
00:39:18,689 --> 00:39:19,899
Yes, that's it.

791
00:39:19,982 --> 00:39:22,362
- Taken before the night he was killed.
- Let's go get him.

792
00:39:35,831 --> 00:39:36,831
<b><font color="#808080">LUCIFER:</font></b> Flanders.

793
00:39:37,416 --> 00:39:38,936
I believe you're looking for this man.

794
00:39:45,174 --> 00:39:48,554
I happened to be walking
past Tiernan's office,

795
00:39:48,636 --> 00:39:51,006
and I overheard him talking about
leaving town.

796
00:39:51,097 --> 00:39:54,387
As a concerned citizen, I felt
it was my civic duty to bring him in...

797
00:39:55,226 --> 00:39:58,226
so he can properly face
the punishment he deserves.

798
00:40:01,023 --> 00:40:02,023
Why did you do it?

799
00:40:03,442 --> 00:40:07,282
Something made me realize
I might have gone a bit too far recently.

800
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:09,406
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SIGHS]</font></b>

801
00:40:09,490 --> 00:40:10,910
Hopefully it's not too late.

802
00:40:13,953 --> 00:40:15,123
You looked.

803
00:40:17,665 --> 00:40:18,825
You looked, didn't you?

804
00:40:22,878 --> 00:40:23,958
<b><font color="#D900D9">[WHISPERING]</font></b> At your wings.

805
00:40:26,173 --> 00:40:27,173
I did.

806
00:40:28,634 --> 00:40:30,304
You did the right thing, Lucifer.

807
00:40:30,678 --> 00:40:32,178
It's never too late for that.

808
00:40:50,948 --> 00:40:51,948
<b><font color="#D900D9">[SIGHS]</font></b>

809
00:40:56,412 --> 00:40:57,412
Maze?

810
00:41:01,667 --> 00:41:02,917
Maze?

811
00:41:03,043 --> 00:41:04,043
What are you doing?

812
00:41:08,757 --> 00:41:10,007
Giving you your space.

813
00:41:11,886 --> 00:41:13,886
I know your heart's in the right place

814
00:41:14,138 --> 00:41:19,308
and it makes me happy knowing my
son's Auntie Maze is in his corner...

815
00:41:19,977 --> 00:41:21,307
but I have to ask.

816
00:41:22,813 --> 00:41:24,063
Are you in love with me?

817
00:41:24,565 --> 00:41:27,275
<b><font color="#D900D9">[LAUGHING]</font></b> What?

818
00:41:29,153 --> 00:41:30,453
I mean...

819
00:41:30,529 --> 00:41:34,489
you do have that good things come
in small packages vibe about you.

820
00:41:35,409 --> 00:41:36,909
But, no, we're just friends.

821
00:41:36,994 --> 00:41:38,204
<b><font color="#D900D9">[LINDA LAUGHS]</font></b>

822
00:41:38,287 --> 00:41:40,207
That's what I thought!

823
00:41:40,289 --> 00:41:41,669
<b><font color="#D900D9">[BOTH LAUGH]</font></b>

824
00:41:43,042 --> 00:41:46,712
You know, Maze, I think you're looking
for something more...

825
00:41:47,922 --> 00:41:50,302
than what this baby or I can be.

826
00:41:50,883 --> 00:41:54,433
I think you're looking for your
own connection.

827
00:41:56,096 --> 00:41:57,256
For a partner.

828
00:41:58,641 --> 00:41:59,641
<b><font color="#D900D9">[PHONE BEEPS]</font></b>

829
00:42:20,579 --> 00:42:21,579
<b><font color="#808080">DAN:</font></b> Hey.

830
00:42:21,622 --> 00:42:23,002
<b><font color="#808080">ELLA:</font></b> Oh, hey.

831
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:25,130
Sorry, I didn't mean to startle you.

832
00:42:25,209 --> 00:42:26,789
Oh, no, it's fine.

833
00:42:27,253 --> 00:42:28,633
Working pretty late tonight.

834
00:42:29,213 --> 00:42:32,223
Oh, yeah, I was just...

835
00:42:32,383 --> 00:42:33,513
wrapping up.

836
00:42:36,136 --> 00:42:37,596
Hey, Ella, do you...

837
00:42:40,349 --> 00:42:42,689
do you ever feel just completely...

838
00:42:44,311 --> 00:42:45,311
Lost?

839
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:47,480
Yeah.

840
00:42:52,027 --> 00:42:53,357
You want to talk about it?

841
00:42:54,905 --> 00:42:55,905
No.

842
00:42:57,449 --> 00:43:00,289
No, honestly, not really.

843
00:43:03,455 --> 00:43:05,615
- You want to talk about it?
- <b><font color="#808080">DAN:</font></b> No.

844
00:43:10,129 --> 00:43:11,839
But I just don't know...

845
00:43:13,632 --> 00:43:15,092
what to do, you know.

846
00:43:15,926 --> 00:43:20,886
Well, I don't recommend a downward
spiral into drugs and alcohol.

847
00:43:20,973 --> 00:43:22,023
<b><font color="#D900D9">[DAN LAUGHS]</font></b>

848
00:43:22,266 --> 00:43:25,136
Tried that, did not help.

849
00:43:25,227 --> 00:43:26,687
<b><font color="#D900D9">[BOTH LAUGH]</font></b>

850
00:43:27,563 --> 00:43:30,983
<b><font color="#D900D9">["CAN YOU HEAR ME" BY UNSECRET PLAYING]</font></b>

851
00:43:37,656 --> 00:43:42,076
<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font> Tell me, can you hear me? <font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

852
00:43:44,538 --> 00:43:48,958
<i><font color="#D900D9">♪</font> I need you to hear me <font color="#D900D9">♪</font></i>

853
00:43:55,049 --> 00:43:56,799
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GATE CLANGS]</font></b>

854
00:44:02,848 --> 00:44:03,928
Detective Decker.

855
00:44:06,268 --> 00:44:07,478
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GATE CLANGS]</font></b>

856
00:44:08,228 --> 00:44:09,398
Thank you for coming.

857
00:44:12,775 --> 00:44:17,485
I only came to tell you to stop
putting in requests to speak to me.

858
00:44:17,571 --> 00:44:19,071
We have nothing to talk about.

859
00:44:19,990 --> 00:44:23,080
I'm sorry... 
I don't have much time.

860
00:44:24,161 --> 00:44:26,911
They're going to transfer
me back to Rome...

861
00:44:27,456 --> 00:44:28,666
to be tried there.

862
00:44:28,874 --> 00:44:29,874
<b><font color="#D900D9">[CHLOE SIGHS]</font></b> Oh.

863
00:44:30,751 --> 00:44:32,711
I can't say I'm sad to see you go.

864
00:44:33,754 --> 00:44:37,724
- There's something you need to know.
- No, there is something you need to know.

865
00:44:38,634 --> 00:44:40,554
You were wrong about Lucifer.

866
00:44:41,178 --> 00:44:43,888
He is a good man.

867
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:48,103
One might say that
he's even an angel.

868
00:44:51,563 --> 00:44:52,563
<b><font color="#808080">LINDA:</font></b> Lucifer?

869
00:44:56,402 --> 00:44:58,652
I came over as soon
as I got your text.

870
00:45:02,866 --> 00:45:03,906
<b><font color="#808080">LINDA:</font></b> It's late.

871
00:45:03,992 --> 00:45:05,992
<b><font color="#D900D9">[LUCIFER SHUDDERING]</font></b>

872
00:45:06,120 --> 00:45:07,540
<b><font color="#808080">LINDA:</font></b> Is everything okay?

873
00:45:09,540 --> 00:45:11,210
You have to help me, doctor.

874
00:45:12,876 --> 00:45:13,876
<b><font color="#D900D9">[LUCIFER SIGHS]</font></b>

875
00:45:14,545 --> 00:45:16,835
<b><font color="#D900D9">[STUTTERING]</font></b>
I don't want to be a monster.

876
00:45:17,506 --> 00:45:18,336
<b><font color="#D900D9">[LUCIFER SIGHS]</font></b>

877
00:45:18,424 --> 00:45:19,424
What's wrong?

878
00:45:19,842 --> 00:45:21,092
It's my wings.

879
00:45:23,387 --> 00:45:27,387
I hadn't checked them
since my devil face returned.

880
00:45:28,100 --> 00:45:30,850
I was afraid they might have gone.

881
00:45:30,936 --> 00:45:32,646
I was afraid what that might mean.

882
00:45:32,730 --> 00:45:34,310
What that might say about me.

883
00:45:35,274 --> 00:45:37,284
But earlier this evening I looked.

884
00:45:38,694 --> 00:45:39,694
And?

885
00:45:40,821 --> 00:45:42,031
They're still there.

886
00:45:44,700 --> 00:45:46,830
That's good. Isn't it?

887
00:45:49,204 --> 00:45:50,584
<b><font color="#808080">FATHER KINLEY:</font></b> I need to warn you

888
00:45:50,789 --> 00:45:52,169
about the prophecy.

889
00:45:52,791 --> 00:45:53,791
Prophecy?

890
00:45:54,334 --> 00:45:58,174
You see, I thought that the
prophecy was about you, Chloe.

891
00:45:58,338 --> 00:46:00,338
But I realize now that
I could have been wrong.

892
00:46:00,507 --> 00:46:05,467
If it's not you, then who else
could be Lucifer's first love?

893
00:46:15,773 --> 00:46:16,773
I saw them.

894
00:46:19,151 --> 00:46:20,361
It was bad.

895
00:46:20,444 --> 00:46:22,074
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GASPING]</font></b>

896
00:46:22,154 --> 00:46:23,454
It was really bad.

897
00:46:28,076 --> 00:46:29,906
You know who it is, don't you?

898
00:46:36,752 --> 00:46:38,002
Is she here?

899
00:46:40,464 --> 00:46:42,174
I thought I could fix it so...

900
00:46:43,175 --> 00:46:45,925
So I didn't hurt him.
I stopped myself.

901
00:46:46,011 --> 00:46:49,221
- So I don't understand why. Why?
- Why what?

902
00:46:50,015 --> 00:46:53,765
<b><font color="#808080">FATHER KINLEY:</font></b> I just need
you to hear the prophecy.

903
00:46:57,147 --> 00:46:58,317
All right.

904
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:03,200
When the devil walks the earth
and finds his first love...

905
00:47:03,737 --> 00:47:05,907
Why are they still like this?!

906
00:47:06,573 --> 00:47:08,373
...evil shall be released.

907
00:47:09,284 --> 00:47:10,624
<b><font color="#D900D9">[WHOOSH]</font></b>

908
00:47:11,245 --> 00:47:13,245
<b><font color="#D900D9">[GASPING]</font></b>

